ADDITIONAL IMPORTANT OPERATIONAL NOTES (2026-03-07)
------------------------------------
Repository and deployment layout
- `repo_deploy` is the git-tracked website frontend and client JS.
- `api` is outside this repo and must be synced manually to server.
- `media` is outside this repo and must be synced manually to server.

Git workflow safety (MEL + Josh collaboration)
- Always run before any work:
  `git -C ~/www/nala-test.com/public_html/repo_deploy pull --ff-only origin main`
- Do feature work in a branch, not directly on `main`.
- Merge to `main` using fast-forward when possible (no force push / no history rewrite).
- If you need a safety snapshot before pulling:
  `git -C ~/www/nala-test.com/public_html/repo_deploy branch codex/backup-YYYY-MM-DD-HHMM`

Registration flow (current behavior)
- Registration form does not collect password in the UI.
- `api/register.php` creates user with `current_lesson = 3` (intro + first 3 lessons access).
- Registration sends password-setup email link to:
  `https://nala-test.com/repo_deploy/set-password/index.html?token=...`
- Password is set through `api/set_password.php`.

SMTP email setup (Google Workspace / Gmail authenticated SMTP)
- Register endpoint uses SMTP auth (not plain `mail()`).
- Required config keys (in env or `config.php`):
  - `NALA_SMTP_HOST` (example: `smtp.gmail.com`)
  - `NALA_SMTP_PORT` (`587` for TLS or `465` for SSL)
  - `NALA_SMTP_ENCRYPTION` (`tls`, `ssl`, or `none`)
  - `NALA_SMTP_USER` (example: `support@nalanetwork.com`)
  - `NALA_SMTP_PASS` (Google App Password)
  - `NALA_SMTP_FROM_EMAIL`
  - `NALA_SMTP_FROM_NAME`
  - `NALA_SMTP_REPLY_TO`
  - `NALA_SMTP_TIMEOUT`

Quick production verification commands
- Check deployed git revision:
  `git -C ~/www/nala-test.com/public_html/repo_deploy rev-parse --short HEAD`
- Confirm register endpoint response:
  `curl -i -sS -X POST https://nala-test.com/api/register.php -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name":"test","email":"your+alias@gmail.com","phone":"1112223333"}'`
- Check API log:
  `tail -n 120 ~/www/nala-test.com/public_html/api/php_errorlog`

Notes about manual sync (non-git folders)
- If `api` files change locally, upload them manually to:
  `~/www/nala-test.com/public_html/api/`
- If `media` files change locally, upload them manually to:
  `~/www/nala-test.com/public_html/media/`
- Do not assume `git pull` updates `api`/`media`.

OPEN TASKS / QA FOLLOW-UP
------------------------------------
- Simplify curriculum resource display:
  if a lesson already contains the main video and images, do not show redundant nested video/image entries that require extra clicks.
- Verify lesson images:
  compare each lesson image/photo against the original website and confirm the correct image is attached to the correct lesson.
- Normalize lesson title style:
  review all lesson titles for grammar and capitalization and make them consistent across the course.
- Verify quiz questions:
  replace any placeholder quiz questions in the database with the correct final questions from the original course content.
- Make the website bilingual:
  add a Spanish version of the website so core navigation, pages, and curriculum can be used in both English and Spanish.
- Fix lesson set/module titles:
  review module titles and ensure they correctly match the lessons they contain (for example, automotive code lessons should not appear under "Commercial Door Hardware").
- Fix quiz visibility:
  investigate and correct quiz items that are currently not visible or readable in the curriculum.
